ttribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Chong, Young, Chun, Hang, Ho, In, Jung, Maeng, Mijin, Rong, Hyong, Pong, Then, Yom, Lanh, Nu.  Cambodian Chea, Chhay, Chheng, Chhom, Voeun, Yoeun.  Spanish Alejandro, Angel, Miguel, Ricardo, Secundino, Tomas.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 阮, see   Ruan   3.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 殷 and 尹, see   Yin   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Ruan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Ping, Xiu, Ying, Biao, Chao, Cheng, Guang, Guohua, Hua, Huiming, Jia, Jian Hua.  Spanish Jorge, Arnulfo, Arturo, Blanca, Carlos, Eduardo, Gregorio, Guillermo, Javier, Jesus, Jose, Josefina.","Irish and Scottish: variant of   Ruane  .","Spanish (<b>Ruán</b>): nickname from <i>ruán</i> ‘roan’ (a color of horses), a variant of   Ruano  ."]}]},{"name":"PONTHIEU","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French:","variant of   Pontier  .","altered form of   Ponthieux  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pontier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Francisco, Mercedes, Osvaldo, Ramon, Roberto.  French Jean-Pierre, Pierre.","French and Dutch: occupational name for a toll keeper on a bridge, from an agent derivative of <i>pont</i> ‘bridge’. This surname is also found in the Dominican Republic.","History: The first recorded bearer of the surname <i>Pontier</i> in the US was Lewis Pontier, born in MD in the 1800s. His origins are not known."]}]},{"name":"Blanche","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname for a blonde, from <i>blanche</i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Blanche DE NOUVION EN PONTHIEU was born in 1181, in Nouvion, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France as the daughter of Jossine De Gamaches. She had at least 1 son with Bernard DE BOUFFLERS. She died in 1235, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1181–1235":"1181–1235","1176–1238":"1176–1238","1168–1225":"1168–1225","1197–1248":"1197–1248","1152–1209":"1152–1209","1238":"1238","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1168":"1168","1176":"1176","1197":"1197","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","1181":"1181","Boufflers, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Boufflers, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Nouvion-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Nouvion, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1181–1235":"1181–1235","1176–1238":"1176–1238","1168–1225":"1168–1225","1197–1248":"1197–1248","1152–1209":"1152–1209","1238":"1238","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1168":"1168","1176":"1176","1197":"1197","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","1181":"1181","Boufflers, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Boufflers, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Nouvion-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Nouvion, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska"},"fr":{"1181–1235":"1181–1235","1176–1238":"1176–1238","1168–1225":"1168–1225","1197–1248":"1197–1248","1152–1209":"1152–1209","1238":"1238","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1168":"1168","1176":"1176","1197":"1197","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","1181":"1181","Boufflers, Abbeville, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Boufflers, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Nouvion-en-Ponthieu, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Nouvion, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","lifeSummary":"Blanche DE NOUVION EN PONTHIEU est née en 1181, à Nouvion, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, fille de Jossine De Gamaches. Elle a eu au moins 